    <div class="container">
        <div class="span7">   
            <div class="about-us">   
                <h1>About Us</h1>
                <br>             
                <p>
                    Niels Henrik David Bohr greatly influenced how current day science works. Next to his contributions in the Solvay conference, he also won a Nobel Price and received several distinctions. This tool is named after him because it will allow you to deliver your best work.  And also because we are great admirers of the work of Bohr (hanging out with Einstein, like a boss).
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    Who are we? We are a group of lonely scientists that wanted to create their own tools. Our promotor said that we would not be able to do it (ha!) so we had to prove him wrong! 
A lot of time and effort has yielded this result, we hope that you enjoy using Bohr. We only want to make money when we can <strong>significantly </strong>improve the quality of your paper or your work (for example if a professional proofreads your paper).
                    <br>
                    <br>Do you want to become an ambassador? Contact us at hello@bohr.ac     
                    </br> 
                </p>
                <br> 
                <p>Here are some tools that we use on a daily basis:</p>
                <br>  
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="http://www.wikicfp.com/cfp/">WikiCFP: find call for papers </a></li>
                    <li><a href="http://journalreviewer.org/">Journal Reviewer </a></li>
                    <li><a href="http://www.researchgate.net/">Researchgate </a></li>
                    <li><a href=" http://www.phdcomics.com/comics.php ">PhD comics </a></li>
                    <li><a href=" http://www.doaj.org/">Overview  of Open Access Journals </a></li>
                </ul>       
                <br>
                <p>Feel free to drop us a line hello@bohr.ac</p>        
            </div>   
        </div>          
