                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-group">
                        <div class="accordion-heading">
                            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseThree">Is Bohr a reference manager?
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-body collapse">
                            <div class="accordion-inner">
                                No, for now you will have to keep using your current reference manager. Google provides a great tool in Google docs: go to Extra: Research (or press Ctrl+Alt+Shift+I) and a toolbar will appear. There you can just search for your article and add your reference.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-group">
                        <div class="accordion-heading">
                            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseFour">Can you give some awesome tips and are there hotkeys?
                            </a>
                        </div>
